zhoneCpeVoipServer.description: Cpe Voip Server for the VoIP feature.

zhoneCpeVoipServerIndexNext.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerIndexNext
zhoneCpeVoipServerIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for the zhoneCpeVoipServerIndex when creating entries in the zhoneCpeVoipServerTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the zhoneCpeVoipServerIndex value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index. After a manager retrieves a value the agent will determine through its local policy when this index value will be made available for reuse.

zhoneCpeVoipServerTable.description: Cpe Voip Server table for the VoIP feature.

zhoneCpeVoipServerIndex.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerIndex
zhoneCpeVoipServerIndex.description: This represents the CPE Voip Server Index value.

zhoneCpeVoipServerRowStatus.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerRowStatus
zhoneCpeVoipServerRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpeVoipProfileName.name: zhoneCpeVoipProfileName
zhoneCpeVoipProfileName.description: CPE Voip Server profile for the VoIP services for the dynamic bridging. This field is only writable upon creation and must be unique within its table.

zhoneCpeVoipPrimaryServer.name: zhoneCpeVoipPrimaryServer
zhoneCpeVoipPrimaryServer.description: This attribute contains the name (IP address or resolved name) of the primary MGC or SIP proxy server that controls the signaling messages.

zhoneCpeVoipSecondaryServer.name: zhoneCpeVoipSecondaryServer
zhoneCpeVoipSecondaryServer.description: This attribute contains the name (IP address or resolved name) of the secondary or backup MGC that controls the signalling messages.

zhoneCpeVoipServerSignallingProtocol.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerSignallingProtocol
zhoneCpeVoipServerSignallingProtocol.description: This attribute specifies the VoIP signalling protocol to use.

zhoneCpeVoipSipRegExpirationTime.name: zhoneCpeVoipSipRegExpirationTime
zhoneCpeVoipSipRegExpirationTime.description: Sip Reg Expiration Time specifies the SIP registration expiration time in seconds. If its value is 0, the SIP agent does not add an expiration time to the registration requests and does not perform re-registration. The default value is 3600 seconds.

zhoneCpeVoipSipReRegHeadStartTime.name: zhoneCpeVoipSipReRegHeadStartTime
zhoneCpeVoipSipReRegHeadStartTime.description: Sip ReReg Head Star Time specifies the time in seconds prior to timeout that causes the SIP agent to start the re-registration process. The default value is 360 seconds.

zhoneCpeVoipSipDomain.name: zhoneCpeVoipSipDomain
zhoneCpeVoipSipDomain.description: This attribute contains the host or domain part of the SIP address of record for users connected to this ONT.

zhoneCpeVoipSipRegistrar.name: zhoneCpeVoipSipRegistrar
zhoneCpeVoipSipRegistrar.description: Sip Registrar points to a network address ME that contains the name (IP 25 address or resolved name) of the registrar server for SIP signalling messages.

zhoneCpeVoipSoftSwitch.name: zhoneCpeVoipSoftSwitch
zhoneCpeVoipSoftSwitch.description: Soft switch identifies the SIP gateway softswitch vendor. The format is four ASCII coded alphabetic characters [A..Z] as defined in ANSI T1.220. A 30 value of four null characters indicates no particular vendor.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcVersion.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcVersion
zhoneCpeVoipMgcVersion.description: This integer attribute reports the version of the Megaco protocol in use.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcMessageFormat.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcMessageFormat
zhoneCpeVoipMgcMessageFormat.description: This attribute defines the message format.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcMaximumRetryTime.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcMaximumRetryTime
zhoneCpeVoipMgcMaximumRetryTime.description: This attribute specifies the maximum retry time for MGC transactions, in seconds. The default value 0 specifies vendor-specific implementation.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcMaximumRetryAttempts.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcMaximumRetryAttempts
zhoneCpeVoipMgcMaximumRetryAttempts.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of times a message is retransmitted to the MGC. The default value 0 specifies vendor specific implementation.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcServiceChangeDelay.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcServiceChangeDelay
zhoneCpeVoipMgcServiceChangeDelay.description: The attribute specifies the service status delay time for changes in line service status. This attribute is specified in seconds. The default value 0 specifies no delay.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcTerminationIdBase.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcTerminationIdBase
zhoneCpeVoipMgcTerminationIdBase.description: The attribute specifies the base string for the H.248 physical termination id(s) for this ONT. This string is intended to uniquely identify an ONT. Vendor specific termination identifiers (i.e. port ids) are optionally added to this string to uniquely identify a termination on a specific ONT.

zhoneCpeVoipReleaseTimer.name: zhoneCpeVoipReleaseTimer
zhoneCpeVoipReleaseTimer.description: This attribute contains a release timer defined in seconds. The value 0 specifies that the ONT is to use its internal default. The default value of this 45 attribute is 10 seconds.

zhoneCpeVoipRohTimer.name: zhoneCpeVoipRohTimer
zhoneCpeVoipRohTimer.description: This attribute defines the time in seconds for the receiver off hook condition before ROH tone is applied. The value 0 disables ROH timing. The default value is 15 seconds.

zhoneCpeVoipDscpMark.name: zhoneCpeVoipDscpMark
zhoneCpeVoipDscpMark.description: Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing RTP packets for this profile. The default value is expedited forwarding (EF) = 0x2E.

zhoneCpeVoipPiggyBackEvents.name: zhoneCpeVoipPiggyBackEvents
zhoneCpeVoipPiggyBackEvents.description: Enables or disables RTP piggyback events.

zhoneCpeVoipOobToneEvents.name: zhoneCpeVoipOobToneEvents
zhoneCpeVoipOobToneEvents.description: Enables or disables handling of tones via RTP tone events per RFC 4733.

zhoneCpeVoipOobDtmfEvents.name: zhoneCpeVoipOobDtmfEvents
zhoneCpeVoipOobDtmfEvents.description: Enables or disables handling of DTMF via RTP DTMF events per RFC 4733.

zhoneCpeVoipOobCasEvents.name: zhoneCpeVoipOobCasEvents
zhoneCpeVoipOobCasEvents.description: Enables or disables handling of CAS via RTP CAS events per RFC 4733.

zhoneCpeVoipPartialDialTimeout.name: zhoneCpeVoipPartialDialTimeout
zhoneCpeVoipPartialDialTimeout.description: This attribute defines the partial dial timeout for digit map processing in milliseconds. The default value is 16000 ms.

zhoneCpeVoipCriticalDialTimeout.name: zhoneCpeVoipCriticalDialTimeout
zhoneCpeVoipCriticalDialTimeout.description: This attribute defines the critical dial timeout for digit map processing in milliseconds. The default value is 4000 ms.

zhoneCpeVoipServerOutboundServer.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerOutboundServer
zhoneCpeVoipServerOutboundServer.description: This attribute contains the name (IP address or resolved name) of the outbound proxy server for SIP signalling messages.

zhoneCpeVoipServerPortId.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerPortId
zhoneCpeVoipServerPortId.description: This attribute specifies the TCP/UDP port number of the VoIP protocol. The default value -1 select the default port number for the VoIP protocol. It is 2944 for H.248 and 5060 for SIP.

zhoneCpeVoipDtmfEventsPassingMethod.name: zhoneCpeVoipDtmfEventsPassingMethod
zhoneCpeVoipDtmfEventsPassingMethod.description: If zhoneCpeVoipOobDtmfEvents is disabled, dtmp digits are carried along the voice path. If zhoneCpeVoipOobDtmfEvents = enabled, we look at the dtmf-events-passing-method. If zhoneCpeVoipDtmfEventsPassingMethod = rfc4733, dtmf digits are carried in the RTP payload. If zhoneCpeVoipDtmfEventsPassingMethod = sip-info, dtmf digits are carried along the signalling path in the INFO messages.

zhoneCpeVoipCasEventsPassingMethod.name: zhoneCpeVoipCasEventsPassingMethod
zhoneCpeVoipCasEventsPassingMethod.description: If zhoneCpeVoipOobCasEvents is disabled, dtmp digits are carried along the voice path. If zhoneCpeVoipOobCasEvents = enabled, we look at the dtmf-events-passing-method. If zhoneCpeVoipCasEventsPassingMethod = rfc4733, dtmf digits are carried in the RTP payload. If zhoneCpeVoipCasEventsPassingMethod = sip-info, dtmf digits are carried along the signalling path in the INFO messages.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcpClientAddressMode.name: zhoneCpeVoipMgcpClientAddressMode
zhoneCpeVoipMgcpClientAddressMode.description: Ip and IpBracketed will cause the MGCP Client name to be the bound voice host IP address. Domain Name will allow the user to input any text string, usally a Domain Name.

zhoneCpeVoipMgcpPersistentNotify.description: When enabled, all switchhook events will be forwarded to the switch immediately without regards to what the switch has requested. When disabled, the event that the switch has requested will be forwarded.

zhoneCpeIpServerPrimaryDns.name: zhoneCpeIpServerPrimaryDns
zhoneCpeIpServerPrimaryDns.description: This attribute specifies the primary DNS IP address. If this value is 0.0.0.0, no primary SIP DNS is defined. The default value is 0.0.0.0

zhoneCpeIpServerSecondaryDns.name: zhoneCpeIpServerSecondaryDns
zhoneCpeIpServerSecondaryDns.description: This attribute specifies the secondary DNS IP address. If this value is 0.0.0.0, no secondary SIP DNS is defined. The default value is 0.0.0.0.

zhoneCpeIpServerFirewallAccess.name: zhoneCpeIpServerFirewallAccess
zhoneCpeIpServerFirewallAccess.description: Lists the protocols allowed on this interface. The firewall option must be enabled before these settings will take effect.

zhoneCpeIpServerNat.name: zhoneCpeIpServerNat
zhoneCpeIpServerNat.description: When it is enabled, NAT/NAPT function is performed to translate between the public IP address and the private addresses. It is only supported on a WAN interface.

zhoneCpeIpServerSecureForward.name: zhoneCpeIpServerSecureForward
zhoneCpeIpServerSecureForward.description: When this mode is enabled, packets are not flooded to all ports. Instead, all packets are forwarded to the port that is designated as the uplink port. In this mode, users are prevented from directly communicating with each other, and broadcast frames are discarded.

zhoneCpeIpServerDefaultIface.name: zhoneCpeIpServerDefaultIface
zhoneCpeIpServerDefaultIface.description: When true, an internally generated packet (e.g., from SNMP trap, SNTP, etc.) is sent out through this interface if the destination IP address is not defined in the route table.

zhoneCpeIpServerDnsSrc.name: zhoneCpeIpServerDnsSrc
zhoneCpeIpServerDnsSrc.description: When true, the Interface is used by the DHCP Client to obtain DNS information.

zhoneCpeIpServerDnsType.name: zhoneCpeIpServerDnsType
zhoneCpeIpServerDnsType.description: Default - Get the DNS information from the WAN interface Static - The DNS information is manually provisioned Proxy - Enable interface to act as a proxy for DNS requests

zhoneCpeVoipFeatures.description: Cpe Voip Features for the VoIP feature.

zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesProfileName.name: zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesProfileName
zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesProfileName.description: CPE Voip Media profile for the dynamic bridging VoIP services. This field is only writable upon creation and must be unique within its table.

zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesAnnouncementType.name: zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesAnnouncementType
zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesAnnouncementType.description: This attribute specifies the treatment when a subscriber goes off hook but does not attempt a call.

zhoneCpeVoipCidFeatures.name: zhoneCpeVoipCidFeatures
zhoneCpeVoipCidFeatures.description: This attribute contains a bit map of caller ID features. By default all the bits are set.

zhoneCpeVoipCallWaitingFeatures.name: zhoneCpeVoipCallWaitingFeatures
zhoneCpeVoipCallWaitingFeatures.description: This attribute contains a bit map of call waiting features. By default all the bits are set.

zhoneCpeVoipCallProgressOrTransferFeatur.name: zhoneCpeVoipCallProgressOrTransferFeatures
zhoneCpeVoipCallProgressOrTransferFeatur.description: This attribute is a bit map of call processing features. By default all the bits are set.

zhoneCpeVoipCallPresentationFeatures.name: zhoneCpeVoipCallPresentationFeatures
zhoneCpeVoipCallPresentationFeatures.description: This attribute is a bit map of call presentation features. By default all the bits are set.

zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesHotLine.name: zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesHotLine
zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesHotLine.description: When the hotline is hot, the phone will immediately dial the Hotline number. When the hotline is warm, the phone wait for the period specified in warmline-timer in ms before automatically dial the hotline number.

zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesHotLineNumber.name: zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesHotLineNumber
zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesHotLineNumber.description: The number this phone will automatically dial, if hotline or warmline feature is enabled.

zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesWarmLineTimer.name: zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesWarmLineTimer
zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesWarmLineTimer.description: The wait period before a warmline automcatically dial the hotline number.

zhoneCpeVoipMediaProfileName.description: CPE Voip Media profile for the dynamic bridging VoIP services. This field is only writable upon creation and must be unique within its table.

zhoneCpeVoipMediaEchoCancel.name: zhoneCpeVoipMediaEchoCancel
zhoneCpeVoipMediaEchoCancel.description: This attribute turns on and off echo cancellation.

zhoneCpeVoipFaxMode.name: zhoneCpeVoipFaxMode
zhoneCpeVoipFaxMode.description: This attribute selects the fax mode.

zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionFirstOrder.name: zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionFirstOrder
zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionFirstOrder.description: This attribute specifies codec selection as defined by RFC 3551.

zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionFirstOr.name: zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionFirstOrder
zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionFirstOr.description: This attribute specifies the packet period selection interval in milliseconds. The default value is 10. Valid values are 10..30 ms.

zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionFirstOrder.name: zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionFirstOrder
zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionFirstOrder.description: This attribute specifies whether silence suppression is on or off.

zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionSecondOrder.name: zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionSecondOrder
zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionSecondOrder.description: This attribute specifies codec selection as defined by RFC 3551.

zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionSecondO.description: This attribute specifies the packet period selection interval in milliseconds. The default value is 10. Valid values are 10..30 ms.

zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionSecondOrde.name: zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionSecondOrder
zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionSecondOrde.description: This attribute specifies whether silence suppression is on or off.

zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionThirdOrder.name: zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionThirdOrder
zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionThirdOrder.description: This attribute specifies codec selection as defined by RFC 3551.

zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionThirdOr.name: zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionThirdOrder
zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionThirdOr.description: This attribute specifies the packet period selection interval in milliseconds. The default value is 10. Valid values are 10..30 ms.

zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionThirdOrder.name: zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionThirdOrder
zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionThirdOrder.description: This attribute specifies whether silence suppression is on or off.

zhoneCpeVoipCodecSelectionFourthOrder.description: This attribute specifies codec selection as defined by RFC 3551.

zhoneCpeVoipPacketPeriodSelectionFourthO.description: This attribute specifies the packet period selection interval in milliseconds. The default value is 10. Valid values are 10..30 ms.

zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionFourthOrde.name: zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionFourthOrder
zhoneCpeVoipSilenceSuppressionFourthOrde.description: This attribute specifies whether silence suppression is on or off.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTable.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTable
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTable.description: Cpe Voip Subscriber table for the VoIP feature.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPortNumber.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPortNumber
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPortNumber.description: This represents the CPE Voip Subscriber Port Number.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberAdminState.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberAdminState
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberAdminState.description: This shows the admin state for the CpeVoipSubscriber.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberDialNumber.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberDialNumber
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberDialNumber.description: This attribute contains the dialing number to make the call.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberDisplayName.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberDisplayName
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberDisplayName.description: This ASCII string attribute defines the customer id used for the display attribute in outgoing SIP messages.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberUserName.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberUserName
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberUserName.description: This attribute contains the SIP user identification used for authentication.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPassword.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPassword
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPassword.description: This attribute contains the SIP password used for authentication.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberImpedance.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberImpedance
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberImpedance.description: This attribute specifies the impedance for the POTS UNI.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberRxGain.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberRxGain
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberRxGain.description: This attribute specifies a gain value for the received signal in the form of a 2s complement number. Valid values are -120 (-12.0 dB) to 60 (+6.0 dB).

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTxGain.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTxGain
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTxGain.description: This attribute specifies a gain value for the transmit signal in the form of a 2s complement number. Valid values are -120 (-12.0 dB) to 60 (+6.0 dB).

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTransmissionPath.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTransmissionPath
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberTransmissionPath.description: This attribute allows setting the POTS UNI either to full-time on-hook transmission or part-time on-hook transmission.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberSignallingCode.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberSignallingCode
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberSignallingCode.description: This attribute specifies the POTS-side signaling.

zhoneCpeVoipServerProfileIndex.name: zhoneCpeVoipServerProfileIndex
zhoneCpeVoipServerProfileIndex.description: This attribute points to the associated cpe-voip-server profile.

zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesProfileIndex.name: zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesProfileIndex
zhoneCpeVoipFeaturesProfileIndex.description: This attribute points to the associated cpe-voip-feature profile.

zhoneCpeVoipMediaProfileIndex.name: zhoneCpeVoipMediaProfileIndex
zhoneCpeVoipMediaProfileIndex.description: This attribute points to the associated cpe-voip-media profile.

zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPhoneFollowsWan.name: zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPhoneFollowsWan
zhoneCpeVoipSubscriberPhoneFollowsWan.description: When enabled the phone will lose power any time the WAN is operation status of down.This will allow line monitoring equipment to detect loss of service.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPortNumber.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPortNumber
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPortNumber.description: This represents the CPE Eth Subscriber Port Number.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberRowStatus.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberRowStatus
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberAdminState.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberAdminState
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberAdminState.description: This attribute activates or deactivates the functions performed by the Ethernet port for this subscriber or put the port in test mode.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberLoopback.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberLoopback
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberLoopback.description: This enables or disables Ethernet loopback.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberRate.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberRate
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberRate.description: This attribute sets the Ethernet port rate.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberDuplex.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberDuplex
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberDuplex.description: This attribute sets the Ethernet port duplex.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberMtu.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberMtu
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberMtu.description: This attribute denotes the maximum frame size allowed across this interface.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPortType.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPortType
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPortType.description: This attribute specifies the Ethernet interface wiring.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPauseTime.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPauseTime
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPauseTime.description: This attribute allows the interface to ask the subscriber terminal to temporarily suspend sending data. Units are in pause quanta (1 pause quantum is 512 bit times of the particular implementation).

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberMode.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberMode
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberMode.description: This attribute specifies whether the Ethernet interface is bridged or derived from an IP router function.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerFeed.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerFeed
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerFeed.description: This attribute controls whether power is provided to an external equipment over the Ethernet interface.

zhoneCpeVideoProfileIndex.name: zhoneCpeVideoProfileIndex
zhoneCpeVideoProfileIndex.description: This object points to the associated video profile.

zhoneCpeTrafficManagementProfileIndex.name: zhoneCpeTrafficManagementProfileIndex
zhoneCpeTrafficManagementProfileIndex.description: This object points to the associated Traffic Management profile. If there is no traffic control for the UNI, set it to 0.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberLineStatusAlarm.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberLineStatusAlarm
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberLineStatusAlarm.description: This field is for enabling/disabling alarm reporting from this CPE UNI.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberAlarmSeverity.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberAlarmSeverity
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberAlarmSeverity.description: This field is for specifying the severity level of all the alarms from this CPE UNI.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerShed.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerShed
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerShed.description: When zhoneCpeSystemCommonPowerShutdownDelay is non-zero and the unit is operating on Battery Power during an AC power outage, this option controls the Enable/Disable state of each Ethernet port. Ports with Power Shedding State as Enabled will remain operational on Battery Power, while Disabled ports will be shut down to conserve battery power.

zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerRange.name: zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerRange
zhoneCpeEthSubscriberPowerRange.description: Maximum PoE ( Power over ethernet ) Power allowed per port. When disabled, no PoE Power will be provided.

zhoneCpeVideoIndexNext.name: zhoneCpeVideoIndexNext
zhoneCpeVideoIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for the zhoneCpeVideoIndex when creating entries in the zhoneCpeVideoTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the zhoneCpeVideoIndex value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index. After a manager retrieves a value the agent will determine through its local policy when this index value will be made available for reuse.

zhoneCpeVideoEntry.name: zhoneCpeVideoEntry
zhoneCpeVideoEntry.description: Row in the Cpe Video table.

zhoneCpeVideoIndex.name: zhoneCpeVideoIndex
zhoneCpeVideoIndex.description: This represents the CPE Video Index.

zhoneCpeGemPort.name: zhoneCpeGemPort
zhoneCpeGemPort.description: This represents the CPE GEM Port Index.

zhoneCpeVlan.name: zhoneCpeVlan
zhoneCpeVlan.description: This represents the CPE Vlan Id.

zhoneCpeVideoRowStatus.name: zhoneCpeVideoRowStatus
zhoneCpeVideoRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpeVideoProfileName.name: zhoneCpeVideoProfileName
zhoneCpeVideoProfileName.description: CPE Video profile for the dynamic bridging. This field is only writable upon creation and must be unique within its table.

zhoneCpeVideoMaxSimultaneousGroups.name: zhoneCpeVideoMaxSimultaneousGroups
zhoneCpeVideoMaxSimultaneousGroups.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of dynamic multicast groups that may be replicated to the client port at any one time. The default value 0 specifies that no administrative limit is to be imposed.

zhoneCpeVideoMaxMulticastBandwidth.name: zhoneCpeVideoMaxMulticastBandwidth
zhoneCpeVideoMaxMulticastBandwidth.description: This attribute specifies the maximum imputed dynamic bandwidth, in bytes per second, that may be delivered to the client port at anyone time. The default value 0 specifies that no administrative limit is to be imposed.

zhoneCpeVideoBandwidthEnforce.name: zhoneCpeVideoBandwidthEnforce
zhoneCpeVideoBandwidthEnforce.description: The default value of this boolean attribute is false, and specifies that attempts to exceed the max multicast bandwidth be counted but honored. The value true specifies that such attempts be counted and denied. The imputed bandwidth value is taken from the dynamic access control list table, both for a new join request and for pre-existing groups.

zhoneCpeVideoIgmpVersion.name: zhoneCpeVideoIgmpVersion
zhoneCpeVideoIgmpVersion.description: This attribute specifies the version of the IGMP to be supported.

zhoneCpeVideoIgmpFunction.name: zhoneCpeVideoIgmpFunction
zhoneCpeVideoIgmpFunction.description: This attribute enables an IGMP function - transparent IGMP snooping only, snooping with proxy reporting (SPR) and IGMP proxy. The function must be consistent with the capabilities specified by the other IGMP configuration attributes.

zhoneCpeVideoImmediateLeave.name: zhoneCpeVideoImmediateLeave
zhoneCpeVideoImmediateLeave.description: This attribute enables or disables the immediate leave function.

zhoneCpeVideoUpstreamIgmpRate.name: zhoneCpeVideoUpstreamIgmpRate
zhoneCpeVideoUpstreamIgmpRate.description: This attribute limits the maximum rate of upstream IGMP traffic. Traffic in excess of this limit is silently discarded. The attribute value is specified in messages/second. The default value 0 imposes no rate limit on this traffic.

zhoneCpeVideoRobustness.name: zhoneCpeVideoRobustness
zhoneCpeVideoRobustness.description: This attribute allows tuning for possible packet loss in the network. The default value 0 causes the ONT to follow the IETF recommendation to copy the robustness value from query messages originating further upstream.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlList.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlList
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlList.description: This attribute points to a access control group list. The default value 0 indicates no control list is used.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlIndexTable.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlIndexTable
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlIndexTable.description: Table of next available index values for CPE video access control profile.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlIndexNext.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlIndexNext
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlIndexNext.description: This represents the next available index value for video access control profile. When 30 cpe-video-access-control profiles are configured this field wil give zero as next available index.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlEntry.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlEntry
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlEntry.description: Row in the Cpe Video Access Control table.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlListIndex.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlListIndex
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlListIndex.description: This represents the CPE Video Access Control List Index.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlEntryIndex.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlEntryIndex
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlEntryIndex.description: This represents the CPE Video Access Control Entry Index.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlRowStatus.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlRowStatus
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlProfileName.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlProfileName
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlProfileName.description: CPE Video profile for the dynamic bridging. This field is only writable upon creation and must be unique within its table.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlType.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlType
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlType.description: This attribute defines the video stream type.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlSrcIp.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlSrcIp
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlSrcIp.description: This is the source IP address. Default value is 0.0.0.0, it specifies that the source IP address is to be ignored.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlDstIpStart.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlDstIpStart
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlDstIpStart.description: Destination IP address of the start of the multicast range. Default value is 0.0.0.0.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlDstIpEnd.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlDstIpEnd
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlDstIpEnd.description: Destination IP address of the end of the multicast range. Default value is 0.0.0.0.

zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlImputedGroupBw.name: zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlImputedGroupBw
zhoneCpeVideoAccessControlImputedGroupBw.description: Expressed in bytes/sec, the imputed group bandwidth is used to decide whether or not to honor a join request in the presence of a max multicast bandwidth limit. The default value 0 effectively allows this table entry to avoid max bandwidth limitations.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberPortNumber.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberPortNumber
zhoneCpePweSubscriberPortNumber.description: This represents the CPE Pwe Subscriber Port Number.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberRowStatus.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberRowStatus
zhoneCpePweSubscriberRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberAdminState.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberAdminState
zhoneCpePweSubscriberAdminState.description: This attribute activates or deactivates the functions performed by the CES port for this subscriber or puts the port in test mode.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberLoopback.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberLoopback
zhoneCpePweSubscriberLoopback.description: This attribute specifies and reports the loopback configuration of the physical interface.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberNearEndPort.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberNearEndPort
zhoneCpePweSubscriberNearEndPort.description: When the pseudowire service is transported via IP, this attribute specifies the port number of the near-end TCP/UDP service. The default value is 57000 + port number.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberFarEndIp.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberFarEndIp
zhoneCpePweSubscriberFarEndIp.description: When the pseudowire service is transported via IP, this attribute specifies the IP or resolved name of the far-end termination point.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberFarEndPort.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberFarEndPort
zhoneCpePweSubscriberFarEndPort.description: When the pseudowire service is transported via IP, this attribute specifies the port number of the far-end TCP/UDP service. The default value is 57000 + port number.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberLineLength.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberLineLength
zhoneCpePweSubscriberLineLength.description: This attribute specifies the length of the twisted pair cable from a DS1 physical UNI to the DSX-1 cross-connect point.

zhoneCpePweProfileIndex.name: zhoneCpePweProfileIndex
zhoneCpePweProfileIndex.description: This attribute points to the associated PWE profile. 1 indicates a default profile is used.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberLineStatusAlarm.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberLineStatusAlarm
zhoneCpePweSubscriberLineStatusAlarm.description: This field is for enabling/disabling alarm reporting from this CPE UNI.

zhoneCpePweSubscriberAlarmSeverity.name: zhoneCpePweSubscriberAlarmSeverity
zhoneCpePweSubscriberAlarmSeverity.description: This field is for specifying the severity level of all the alarms from this CPE UNI.

zhoneCpePweIndexNext.name: zhoneCpePweIndexNext
zhoneCpePweIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for the zhoneCpePweIndex when creating entries in the zhoneCpePweTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the zhoneCpePweIndex value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After a manager retrieves a value the agent will determine through its local policy when this index value will be made available for reuse.

zhoneCpePweIndex.name: zhoneCpePweIndex
zhoneCpePweIndex.description: This represents the CPE Pwe Index.

zhoneCpePweRowStatus.name: zhoneCpePweRowStatus
zhoneCpePweRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpePweProfileName.name: zhoneCpePweProfileName
zhoneCpePweProfileName.description: CPE Pwe profile for the dynamic bridging. This field is only writable upon creation and must be unique within its table.

zhoneCpePweLineType.name: zhoneCpePweLineType
zhoneCpePweLineType.description: This attribute specifies the line type (T1, E1 or other) used.

zhoneCpePweEncoding.name: zhoneCpePweEncoding
zhoneCpePweEncoding.description: This attribute specifies the line coding scheme.

zhoneCpePweDs1Mode.name: zhoneCpePweDs1Mode
zhoneCpePweDs1Mode.description: This attribute specifies the mode of a DS1.

zhoneCpePweDs1Framing.name: zhoneCpePweDs1Framing
zhoneCpePweDs1Framing.description: This attribute specifies the DS1 framing structure.

zhoneCpePweTransport.name: zhoneCpePweTransport
zhoneCpePweTransport.description: The underlying transport for the Pseudowire service.

zhoneCpePweServiceType.name: zhoneCpePweServiceType
zhoneCpePweServiceType.description: This attribute specifies the basic service type, either a transparent bit pipe or an encapsulation that recognizes the underlying structure of the payload.

zhoneCpePweSignalling.name: zhoneCpePweSignalling
zhoneCpePweSignalling.description: This attribute specifies how CAS signalling is carried.

zhoneCpePwePayloadSize.name: zhoneCpePwePayloadSize
zhoneCpePwePayloadSize.description: Number of payload bytes per packet. Valid only if service type = unstructured or unstructured octet-aligned. Valid choices depend on the TDM service, but must include the following. Other choices are at the vendor's discretion. DS1 192 DS1 200, required only if unstructured octet aligned service is supported E1 256 DS3 1024 E3 1024

zhoneCpePwePayloadEncapsulationDelay.name: zhoneCpePwePayloadEncapsulationDelay
zhoneCpePwePayloadEncapsulationDelay.description: This represents number of 125 microsecond frames to be encapsulated in each pseudowire packet. Valid only if service type = structured. The minimum set of choices for various TDM services is listed below, and is affected by the possible presence of in-band signalling. Other choices are at the vendor discretion. NxDS0, no signalling, N = 1 64 (8 ms) required, 40 (5 ms) desired NxDS0, no signalling, N = 2..4 32 (4 ms) NxDS0, no signalling, N > 4 8 (1 ms) NxDS0 with DS1 CAS 24 (3 ms) NxDS0 with E1 CAS 16 (2 ms)

zhoneCpePweTimingMode.name: zhoneCpePweTimingMode
zhoneCpePweTimingMode.description: This attribute selects the timing mode of the TDM service. If RTP is used, this attribute must be set to be consistent with the value of the RTP time stamp mode attribute in the RTP parameters managed entity at the far end. 1 Network timing 2 Differential timing 3 Adaptive timing (default) 4 Loop timing: local TDM transmit clock derived from local TDM receive stream

zhoneCpePweChannelAssign.name: zhoneCpePweChannelAssign
zhoneCpePweChannelAssign.description: If service type is structured, this attribute is a bit field indicating the 64kbps sub channels are used. This is not supported currently. The default value is channel0, but it might change later.

zhoneCpePweClockReference.name: zhoneCpePweClockReference
zhoneCpePweClockReference.description: This attribute specifies the frequency of the common timing reference, in multiples of 8 kHz. The default value is 1 (8 kHz).

zhoneCpePweRtpTimeStampMode.name: zhoneCpePweRtpTimeStampMode
zhoneCpePweRtpTimeStampMode.description: This attribute determines the mode in which RTP timestamps are generated in the TDM to PSN direction.

zhoneCpePwePtypePayload.name: zhoneCpePwePtypePayload
zhoneCpePwePtypePayload.description: This attribute specifies the RTP payload type for the payload channel in the TDM to PSN direction. Assignable PTYPEs lie in the dynamic range 96..127.

zhoneCpePwePtypeSignalling.name: zhoneCpePwePtypeSignalling
zhoneCpePwePtypeSignalling.description: This attribute specifies the RTP payload type direction for the signaling channel in the TDM to PSN. Assignable PTYPEs lie in the dynamic range 96..127. If signalling is not transported in its own channel, the value should be set to 0. So the valid values used are 0, 96-127.

zhoneCpePweSSrcPayload.name: zhoneCpePweSSrcPayload
zhoneCpePweSSrcPayload.description: This attribute specifies the RTP synchronization source for the payload channel in the TDM to PSN direction.

zhoneCpePweSSrcSignalling.name: zhoneCpePweSSrcSignalling
zhoneCpePweSSrcSignalling.description: This attribute specifies the RTP synchronization source for the signaling channel in the TDM to PSN direction. If signalling is not transported in its own channel, this value should be set to 0.

zhoneCpePweExpectedPTypePayload.name: zhoneCpePweExpectedPTypePayload
zhoneCpePweExpectedPTypePayload.description: This attribute specifies the RTP payload type for the payload channel in the PSN to TDM direction. The received payload type may be used to detect malformed packets. To disable the check functions, set the value to its default value 0.

zhoneCpePweExpectedPTypeSignalling.name: zhoneCpePweExpectedPTypeSignalling
zhoneCpePweExpectedPTypeSignalling.description: This attribute specifies the RTP payload type for the signaling channel in the PSN to TDM direction. The received payload type may be used to detect malformed packets. To disable the check functions, set the value to its default value 0.

zhoneCpePweExpectedSSrcPayload.name: zhoneCpePweExpectedSSrcPayload
zhoneCpePweExpectedSSrcPayload.description: This attribute specifies the RTP synchronization source in the PSN to TDM direction. The received SSRC may be used to detect misconnection (stray packets). To disable the check functions, set the value to its default value 0.

zhoneCpePweExpectedSSrcSignalling.name: zhoneCpePweExpectedSSrcSignalling
zhoneCpePweExpectedSSrcSignalling.description: This attribute specifies the RTP synchronization source for the signalling channel in the PSN to TDM direction. The received SSRC may be used to detect misconnection (stray packets). To disable the check functions, set the value to its default value 0.

zhoneCpePweJitterBufMax.name: zhoneCpePweJitterBufMax
zhoneCpePweJitterBufMax.description: This attribute specifies the desired maximum depth of the playout buffer in the PSN to TDM direction. The value is expressed as a multiple of the 125 micro second frame rate. The value 0 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweJitterBufDesired.name: zhoneCpePweJitterBufDesired
zhoneCpePweJitterBufDesired.description: This attribute specifies the desired nominal fill depth of the playout buffer in the PSN to TDM direction. The value is expressed as a multiple of the 125 micro second frame rate. The value 0 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweFillPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweFillPolicy
zhoneCpePweFillPolicy.description: This attribute defines the payload bit pattern to be applied toward the TDM service if no payload packet is available to play out. The default value 1 specifies that the ONT apply its internal policy, ie vendor-specific.

zhoneCpePweMisconnectedDeclarePolicy.name: zhoneCpePweMisconnectedDeclarePolicy
zhoneCpePweMisconnectedDeclarePolicy.description: The alarm declaration policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the corresponding alarm to be declared. It is an integer percentage between 1..100. If this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm onset soak interval, the alarm is declared. The default value 0 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweMisconnectedClearPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweMisconnectedClearPolicy
zhoneCpePweMisconnectedClearPolicy.description: The alarm clear policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the correcponding alarm to be cleared. It is an integer percentage between 0..99. If no more than this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm clear soak interval, the alarm is cleared. The default value 255 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweLossPacketDeclarePolicy.name: zhoneCpePweLossPacketDeclarePolicy
zhoneCpePweLossPacketDeclarePolicy.description: The alarm declaration policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the corresponding alarm to be declared. It is an integer percentage between 1..100. If this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm onset soak interval, the alarm is declared. The default value 0 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweLossPacketClearPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweLossPacketClearPolicy
zhoneCpePweLossPacketClearPolicy.description: The alarm clear policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the correcponding alarm to be cleared. It is an integer percentage between 0..99. If no more than this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm clear soak interval, the alarm is cleared. The default value 255 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweOverrunUnderrunDeclarePolicy.name: zhoneCpePweOverrunUnderrunDeclarePolicy
zhoneCpePweOverrunUnderrunDeclarePolicy.description: The alarm declaration policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the corresponding alarm to be declared. It is an integer percentage between 1..100. If this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm onset soak interval, the alarm is declared. The default value 0 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweOverrunUnderrunClearPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweOverrunUnderrunClearPolicy
zhoneCpePweOverrunUnderrunClearPolicy.description: The alarm clear policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the correcponding alarm to be cleared. It is an integer percentage between 0..99. If no more than this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm clear soak interval, the alarm is cleared. The default value 255 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweMalformedDeclarePolicy.name: zhoneCpePweMalformedDeclarePolicy
zhoneCpePweMalformedDeclarePolicy.description: The alarm declaration policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the corresponding alarm to be declared. It is an integer percentage between 1..100. If this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm onset soak interval, the alarm is declared. The default value 0 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweMalformedClearPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweMalformedClearPolicy
zhoneCpePweMalformedClearPolicy.description: The alarm clear policy attribute defines the anomaly rate that causes the correcponding alarm to be cleared. It is an integer percentage between 0..99. If no more than this density of anomalies occurs during the alarm clear soak interval, the alarm is cleared. The default value 255 selects the ONT's internal policy.

zhoneCpePweRBitTransmitSetPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweRBitTransmitSetPolicy
zhoneCpePweRBitTransmitSetPolicy.description: This attribute defines the number of consecutive lost packets that causes the transmitted R bit to be set in the TDM to PSN direction, indicating lost packets to the far end. The default value 0 selects the ONT internal policy.

zhoneCpePweRBitTransmitClearPolicy.name: zhoneCpePweRBitTransmitClearPolicy
zhoneCpePweRBitTransmitClearPolicy.description: This attribute defines the number of consecutive valid packets that causes the transmitted R bit to be cleared in the TDM to PSN direction, removing the remote failure indication to the far end. The default value 0 selects the ONT internal policy.

zhoneCpePweRBitReceivePolicy.name: zhoneCpePweRBitReceivePolicy
zhoneCpePweRBitReceivePolicy.description: This attribute defines the action toward the Nx64 TDM interface when remote failure is indicated on packets received from the PSN.

zhoneCpePweLBitReceivePolicy.name: zhoneCpePweLBitReceivePolicy
zhoneCpePweLBitReceivePolicy.description: This attribute defines the action toward the TDM interface when far end TDM failure is indicated on packets received from the PSN.

zhoneCpePweSesThreshold.name: zhoneCpePweSesThreshold
zhoneCpePweSesThreshold.description: Number of lost, malformed or otherwise unusable packets expected in the PSN to TDM direction within a one-second interval that causes a severely errored second to be counted. Stray packets do not count toward a severely errored second, nor do packets whose L bit is set at the far end. The default value is 3.

zhoneCpePweCdvTolerance.name: zhoneCpePweCdvTolerance
zhoneCpePweCdvTolerance.description: This attribute represents the duration of user data that must be buffered by the CES interworking entity to offset packet delay variation. It is expressed in 10 microsecond increments. The default value for DS1 CES is 750 micro seconds; for DS3 CES, it is 1000 micro seconds.

zhoneCpePweChannelAssociatedSignalling.name: zhoneCpePweChannelAssociatedSignalling
zhoneCpePweChannelAssociatedSignalling.description: This attribute selects the signalling format. It applies to structured interfaces only.

zhoneCpePweMplsTpType.name: zhoneCpePweMplsTpType
zhoneCpePweMplsTpType.description: This attribute specifies the type of ANI-side termination for the MPLS Pseudowire.

zhoneCpePweDscp.name: zhoneCpePweDscp
zhoneCpePweDscp.description: This parameter indicates DSCP value for cpe pwe traffic. Valid code values: <0-63> Differentiated services codepoint value af11 Mark packets with AF11 dscp (001010) af12 Mark packets with AF12 dscp (001100) af13 Mark packets with AF13 dscp (001110) af21 Mark packets with AF21 dscp (010010) af22 Mark packets with AF22 dscp (010100) af23 Mark packets with AF23 dscp (010110) af31 Mark packets with AF31 dscp (011010) af32 Mark packets with AF32 dscp (011100) af33 Mark packets with AF33 dscp (011110) af41 Mark packets with AF41 dscp (100010) af42 Mark packets with AF42 dscp (100100) af43 Mark packets with AF43 dscp (100110) cs1 Mark packets with CS1(precedence 1) dscp (001000) cs2 Mark packets with CS2(precedence 2) dscp (010000) cs3 Mark packets with CS3(precedence 3) dscp (011000) cs4 Mark packets with CS4(precedence 4) dscp (100000) cs5 Mark packets with CS5(precedence 5) dscp (101000) cs6 Mark packets with CS6(precedence 6) dscp (110000) cs7 Mark packets with CS7(precedence 7) dscp (111000) default Mark packets with default dscp (000000) ef Mark packets with EF dscp (101110)

zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoRGBridged.name: zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoRGBridged
zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoRGBridged.description: If TRUE, layer 2 bridging can only be configured via a RG management interface such as SNMP, TR-69, CLI or Web UI. Otherwise, VoIP can be configured via OMCI as well.

zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoRgPwe.name: zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoRgPwe
zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoRgPwe.description: If TRUE, PWE can only be configured via a RG management interface such as SNMP, TR-69, CLI or Web UI. Otherwise, PWE can be configured via OMCI as well.

zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoTftpDnld.name: zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoTftpDnld
zhoneCpeOnuModelInfoTftpDnld.description: If TRUE, then this model support software image download via TFTP. Otherwise, only OMCI downloads are supported.

zhoneCpeOnuSipSupported.description: This represents whether Sip is supported on this ONU.

zhoneCpeOnuH248Supported.description: This represents whether H248 is supported on this ONU.

zhoneCpeTpIndex.description: TpIndex identifies the Index of termination point associated with this MAC bridge port.

zhoneCpeConnectionVlanTpId.description: The value of the tag protocol identifier that is being used for QinQ packets. (0x8100 is default.). Valid values are : 1. 33024 ( 0x8100 ) 2. 34984 ( 0x88A8 ) 3. 37120 ( 0x9100 ) 4. 37376 ( 0x9200 )

zhoneCpeConnectionRgMode.description: Use to specify the RG service for a CPE. zhoneCpeConnectionGuidedVlanId.name: zhoneCpeConnectionGuidedVlanId
zhoneCpeConnectionGuidedVlanId.description: The Guided VLAN Id for RG Services. A zero value means a guided vlan does not exist. If a guided vlan is used then uni-vlan and uni-slan values must be zero.

zhoneCpeConnectionGuidedCos.name: zhoneCpeConnectionGuidedCos

zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndexNext.name: zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndexNext
zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for the zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndex when creating entries in the zhoneCpeTrafficManagementTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndex value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index. After a manager retrieves a value the agent will determine through its local policy when this index value will be made available for reuse.

zhoneCpeTrafficManagementEntry.name: zhoneCpeTrafficManagementEntry
zhoneCpeTrafficManagementEntry.description: Row in the Cpe Traffic Management table.

zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndex.name: zhoneCpeTrafficManagementIndex

zhoneCpeTrafficManagementUpstreamPIR.name: zhoneCpeTrafficManagementUpstreamPIR

zhoneCpeWlanAdvDot1nClientOnly.description: Enable or disable the restriction of access to 802.11n clients, only. When enabled, prevent 802.11b/g clients from connecting.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvRate54G.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvRate54G
zhoneCpeWlanAdvRate54G.description: The rate when the radio is operating in 802.11g mode. This object only applies when the Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) 802.11n Rate is set to use 54g.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvMcastRate.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvMcastRate
zhoneCpeWlanAdvMcastRate.description: The rate for the multicast traffic.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvBasicRate.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvBasicRate
zhoneCpeWlanAdvBasicRate.description: The rate when the radio is operating in basic 802.11b/g mode.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvFragmentationThreshold.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvFragmentationThreshold
zhoneCpeWlanAdvFragmentationThreshold.description: The threshold at which the packets are fragmented.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvRtsThreshold.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvRtsThreshold
zhoneCpeWlanAdvRtsThreshold.description: The packet size of a request-to-send (RTS) transmission. A low threshold implies RTS packets are sent more frequently, thus requiring more bandwidth but ensuring packet transmission on a busy network.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvDtimInterval.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvDtimInterval
zhoneCpeWlanAdvDtimInterval.description: The interval at which Delivery Traffic Indication Messages (DTIM) are generated. A DTIM message notifies a wireless client that a packet is waiting for transmission.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvBeaconInterval.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvBeaconInterval
zhoneCpeWlanAdvBeaconInterval.description: The interval at which Beacons are generated.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvGlobalMaxClients.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvGlobalMaxClients
zhoneCpeWlanAdvGlobalMaxClients.description: The maximum number of wireless client devices that may be simultaneously connected to the radio. This value should include the sum total of all active SSIDs.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvXpressTechnology.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvXpressTechnology
zhoneCpeWlanAdvXpressTechnology.description: Enable or disable the XPress(TM) Technology.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvTxPower.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvTxPower
zhoneCpeWlanAdvTxPower.description: The percentage of total power that should be used for data transmissions.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmm.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmm
zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmm.description: Enable or disable Wifi Multimedia. When set to TRUE, audio, video and voice application data is prioritized over other network traffic.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmmNoAck.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmmNoAck
zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmmNoAck.description: Enable or disable the suppression of acknowledgements for frames that do not require a QOS Acknowledgement. This avoids the unnecessary transmission of acknowledgements for highly time-critical data.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmmApsd.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmmApsd
zhoneCpeWlanAdvWmmApsd.description: Enable or disable the Automatic Power Save Delivery (APSD) power management method. This feature is useful for bi-directional applications, such as VoIp phones.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvBridgeRestrict.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvBridgeRestrict
zhoneCpeWlanAdvBridgeRestrict.description: Wireless Bridge Restriction Modes of operation.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvWps.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvWps
zhoneCpeWlanAdvWps.description: Enable or disable WiFi Protected Setup (WPS) security method. If WPS is enabled, the network authentication method, the data encryption, and network key should also be configured in order to authenticate to this wireless network. It is available for WPA-PSK, WPA2-PSK, Mixed WPA2/WPA-PSK and Open Network Authentication methods.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvWpsAddClientMethod.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvWpsAddClientMethod
zhoneCpeWlanAdvWpsAddClientMethod.description: A client can be added via three different methods.

zhoneCpeWlanAdvWpsApMode.name: zhoneCpeWlanAdvWpsApMode
zhoneCpeWlanAdvWpsApMode.description: If the provider is using an external registrar for security, select configured. The PIN for AP mode is specified by the registrar. Provide this PIN to the client. Issue Config AP to begin the registration process with the client.

zhoneCpeCondiDhcpSrvListIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for the zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvListIndex when creating entries in the zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvListTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. After a manager retrieves a value the agent will determine through its local policy when this index value will be made available for reuse.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvListTable.description: Table in which each entry is a list of conditional dhcp server rules.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvListIndex.description: Index number for this cpe conditional dhcp server list. This is the number that goes into the cpe-dhcp-server record.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvListRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify or delete an entry in this table.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvListProfileName.description: Profile name for this cpe-cond-dhcp-srv-list profile. This must be unique, and is writable only on creation.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvIndexEntry.description: Row in the conditional DHCP server index table.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvIndexEntryIndexNext.description: Next available index for a conditional DHCP server list.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvEntry.description: Row inf the conditional DHCP server table

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvEntryIndex.description: The entry index within the conditional DHCP server list

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvRowStatus.description: The row status for adding and deleting rows.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvAdminState.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvAdminState
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvAdminState.description: Enable/disable this rule. Disabling allows rule to be temporarily unavailable for testing or debug purposes.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriorityOrder.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriorityOrder
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriorityOrder.description: When multiple Conditional DHCP Rules are applied to the same physical port and an ingress packet matches more than one rule, the rule with the highest Priority will be applied. The default priority is for rules to be applied in the order created.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpVciOui.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpVciOui
zhoneCpeCondDhcpVciOui.description: This field is for Vendor Class Identifier (Option 60) or Organizationally Unique Identifier. Conditional DHCP Rules classify ingress packets based on a matching OUI, or based on a matching DHCP Option 60 string value. OUI is the first 3 bytes of a MAC, separated by colons (e.g. 00:02:71). VCI is the text string included in the Option 60. When an attached device sends a DHCP Discover packet to request a dynamically assigned IP Address, it may include this Option 60 string to identify what type of device it is.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvVciMatch.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvVciMatch
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvVciMatch.description: VCI, the Option 60 String included in the DHCP Discover packet, may be up to 255 characters long, while the vci-oui field supports a maximum of 32 characters. This configuration option specifies where to look in the entire Option 60 string for a match. Choices are at the beginning (Prefix), at the end (Suffix), or anywhere in the string (Substring).

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvStartAddr.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvStartAddr
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvStartAddr.description: Starting IP Address for the subnet range associated with this rule. Must be in the same subnet as the LAN IP Interface for this VLAN. Every Conditional DHCP Rule should have a unique range of IP Addresses within the LAN Subnet (non-overlapping).

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvEndAddr.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvEndAddr
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvEndAddr.description: Last ip address associated with this rule.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvWanVlan.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvWanVlan
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvWanVlan.description: VLAN ID of the WAN interface that shall be used as the default forwarding path for all packets received with an IP address in this subnet. This feature enables automatic forwarding of packets sourced by a Conditional DHCP Client device to a different Default Gateway (based on the VLAN ID).

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPortFwdRule.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPortFwdRule
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPortFwdRule.description: When enabled, a Static Port Forwarding Firewall Rule will automatically be created for each client device assigned an IP Address based on this rule.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvStartPort.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvStartPort
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvStartPort.description: WAN-side Port Number of the Port Forwarding Rule that will be automatically created for the Conditional DHCP client assigned the Starting IP Address defined for this rule. The WAN-side Port Number will increment by 1 for each new client device.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPrivatePort.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPrivatePort
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPrivatePort.description: The LAN-side Port Number of the Port Forwarding Rule that will be bound to the private IP Address assigned to each client. This Port Number is typically assigned based on the application that the Port Forwarding Rule will be used for. For example, if the Rule will be used to enable on-demand SSH connections to client devices with conditional IP Addresses, then the Private Port will be 22.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvProtocol.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvProtocol
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvProtocol.description: Defines what type of packets will be allowed through the Static Port Forwarding Rule.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriDns.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriDns
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriDns.description: Defines the Option 6 Primary DNS IP Addresses that will be included in the DHCP Offer to Conditional DHCP client devices matching this rule.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvSecDns.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvSecDns
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvSecDns.description: Defines the Option 6 Secondary DNS IP Addresses that will be included in the DHCP Offer to Conditional DHCP client devices matching this rule.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriNpt.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriNpt
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPriNpt.description: Defines the Option 42 Primary NTP IP Addresses that will be included in the DHCP Offer to Conditional DHCP client devices matching this rule. NOTE that Option 2 (Timezone Offset) will also be included in the DHCP Offer. The Option 2 value will be automatically populated by the ONT, based on what it was assigned on an uplink interface with DHCP client enabled.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvSecNpt.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvSecNpt
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvSecNpt.description: Defines the Option 42 Secondary NTP IP Addresses that will be included in the DHCP Offer to Conditional DHCP client devices matching this rule.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvVsi.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvVsi
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvVsi.description: Vendor Specific Information (Option 43) is a user-configured text string of up to 32 characters with no restrictions on format or content. Required by some DHCP client devices for specific applications and/or boot up procedures.

zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPermanent.name: zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPermanent
zhoneCpeCondDhcpSrvPermanent.description: When enabled, IP Addresses are permanently bound to the MAC address of the device they are assigned to. DHCP Lease table will show permanent entries for each host.

zhoneCpeCmdOperation.name: zhoneCpeCmdOperation
zhoneCpeCmdOperation.description: The Command operation to be performed. The command operation will determine which of the other zhoneCpeCmd objects will be used. The DELETE commands delete configuration. The MOVE commands copy configuration from source to destination. Source configuration is deleted. The CLONE commands copy configuration from source to destination. Source configuration is perserved. Destination configuration befor clone operation is deleted. The APPLY commands copy configuration from source to destination. Source configuration is perserved. Destination configuration prior to appy operation is preserved.

zhoneCpeCmdSrcIfIndex.name: zhoneCpeCmdSrcIfIndex
zhoneCpeCmdSrcIfIndex.description: Command SOURCE ifIndex. Using this object overwrites source shelf/slot/port/subPort objects. This object must be used for virtual CPEs.

zhoneCpeCmdDstIfIndex.name: zhoneCpeCmdDstIfIndex
zhoneCpeCmdDstIfIndex.description: Command DESTINATION ifIndex. Using this object overwrites destination shelf/slot/port/subPort objects. This object must be used for virtual CPEs.

zhoneCpeCmdString.name: zhoneCpeCmdString

zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateVirtualConn.name: zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateVirtualConn
zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateVirtualConn.description: Command cpe service template source CPE ifIndex. Also known as the virutal CPE ifIndex.

zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateTpType.name: zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateTpType
zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateTpType.description: Command cpe service tpType. A zero value means all TpTypes on the destination CPE.

zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateTpIndex.description: Command cpe service DESTINATION tpIndex. A zero value means all UNI ports of the destination CPE.

zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateVlan.description: Command cpe service VLAN, consisting of vlan cos (high order 16 bits) and vlan ID (low order 16 bits).

zhoneCpeCmdSvcTemplateSlan.description: Command cpe service SLAN, consisting of slan cos (high order 16 bits) and slan ID (low order 16 bits).

zhoneCpeCmdOverrideTpIndex.name: zhoneCpeCmdOverrideTpIndex
zhoneCpeCmdOverrideTpIndex.description: If set, use this as the uni number to which the service on the target CPE is applied.

zhoneCpeCmdOverrideVlanId.name: zhoneCpeCmdOverrideVlanId
zhoneCpeCmdOverrideVlanId.description: If set, use this vlanId on the destination CPE.

zhoneCpeCmdOverrideVlanCos.name: zhoneCpeCmdOverrideVlanCos
zhoneCpeCmdOverrideVlanCos.description: If set, use this value as the vlan cos on the destination CPE.

zhoneCpeCmdOverrideSlanId.name: zhoneCpeCmdOverrideSlanId
zhoneCpeCmdOverrideSlanId.description: If set, use this slanId on the destination CPE.

zhoneCpeCmdOverrideSlanCos.name: zhoneCpeCmdOverrideSlanCos
zhoneCpeCmdOverrideSlanCos.description: If set, use this slan cos on the destination CPE.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleIndex.description: This represents the index in the auto-cfg-rule table.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleAdminState.description: If down, this rule will not participate in rule matching.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRulePriority.name: zhoneCpeAutoCfgRulePriority
zhoneCpeAutoCfgRulePriority.description: 1 is the lowest priority. When conflicting rules match, the one with the hightest priority is used.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleMatchExpression.name: zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleMatchExpression
zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleMatchExpression.description: Logical expression telling which CPEs should be configured according to this rule. elements are: keyword followed by value. Multiple elements can be connected with AND. Keywords are: model - specified model ID slot - specifies slot number or numbers olt - specifies GPON OLT number or numbers example: model 2426 AND slot 6 AND olt 1-4,7 In this example, apply to model 2426 discovered on olts 1, 2, 3, 4, or 7 on slot 6.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleServiceTemplate.name: zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleServiceTemplate
zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleServiceTemplate.description: The ifIndex of the virtual ONU supplying the service template for this rule.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleTargetUni.name: zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleTargetUni
zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleTargetUni.description: Which unis from the template should be applied by this rule. This consists of a uni type followed by one or more uni numbers, separated by commas, or with ranges indicated by '-'. The word 'all' may be used to indicate all ports of that type. example: eth 1-3 In this example, apply services on the provisioned ethernet port on the service template to ethernet ports 1, 2, and 3 of the matched CPE. If this field is blank, then the entire service template is applied to the CPE.

zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleDeleteBeforeApply.name: zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleDeleteBeforeApply
zhoneCpeAutoCfgRuleDeleteBeforeApply.description: If true, any existing services on the target unis are removed prior to applying the service template. If the targetUni field is blank and this field is true, then all services on the CPE are removed before the service template is applied.
